					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11088131#post-4216115</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11088131/scp-3657#post-4216115</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 11 Apr 2019 18:25:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Ellie3</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3656445</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Faraday, I'm assuming it's because that if they are caffeinated, they don't feel the need to, well, go inside of the coffee shop. They most likely just want to make sure their staff won't want to mess around with the anomaly.</p> <p>It's not mysterious or a mistake, it's fairly logical, actually.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11088131#post-4215949</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11088131/scp-3657#post-4215949</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 11 Apr 2019 15:12:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Faraday Cage</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1856658</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>At no point is it ever explained (either directly or indirectly) why Foundation personnel need to be pre-caffeinated before they handle the object.</p> <p>I cannot tell if this is on purpose to make things &quot;mysterious&quot; or if it is an accidental mistake.</p> <p>I can tell you that it is the reason I am down-voting. Whether on purpose or not, either way the dangling loose end reads to me as poorly executed and aggravatingly unnecessary.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
